description:
&lt;p&gt;This post is for a B5 Childrens Epilepsy Nurse based within the Childrens Community Nursing Team that covers East Kent. The successful applicant will be supporting our B7 Specialist Epilepsy Nurse and the role will include coordinating care planning, reviewing patients virtually or face to face, training education settings, attending multiagency meetings for the caseload and working alongside paediatrician clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Epilepsy Team helps children and young people to manage their Epilepsy by providing education and support and working with their families. We see children in their homes, education setting, clinics or hospital. The team offer advice on how to give emergency medication where prescribed. We also work with other health professionals and agencies to ensure the best outcomes for children with this condition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base will be Capital House but some remote home working will be an option during covid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KCHFT is an exciting place to work and were awarded an outstanding rating by CQC in 2019. The role will come with a robust trainnig programme and the successful applicant will be offered a period of probation, clinical supervision, a workplace buddy and regular 1:1&#39;s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held &lt;strong&gt;17th November 2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
